      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Zero-pressure accumulation (ZPA) maintains gaps between every product with no contact. Minimum-pressure accumulation allows light product-to-product contact within zones, typically 2-5 lbs of backpressure. ZPA requires more zones and sensors per linear foot, increasing cost by 20-40% over minimum-pressure. ZPA is required for fragile or pressure-sensitive products. Minimum-pressure is acceptable for durable products like corrugated cases."
      }
